Uralkali Trader Sells $140 Million Potash to Vietnam, Belta Says

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-11-29T13:31:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/uralkali-trader-sells-140-million-potash-to-vietnam-belta-says.html
OAO Uralkali’s  export trader
 Belarusian Potash Co.  signed contracts to supply at least $140
million of potash to  Vietnam  next year, Minsk-based Belta
newswire reported citing the company.  The trader known as BPC will supply 150,000 metric tons to
Vietnam’s Apromaco and 125,000 tons to Hanexim, the newswire
said, citing Chief Executive Officer Vladimir Nikolaenko. Filipp
Gritskov, a BPC spokesman in Minsk, confirmed the report.  BPC plans to sign more contracts for as much as 200,000
tons of deliveries to Vietnam in the coming days, Belta reported
citing Nikolaenko.  BPC said Aug. 18 it set potash spot prices for  Southeast
Asia  at $535 a ton from October, according to a statement on its
website. The trader is Uralkali’s joint venture with Belarusian
producer Belaruskali.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  